nsider.com%2Fwoman-housetruck-woods-washes-hair-freezing-criticism-eco-friendly-products-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Viewers%20were%20impressed%20by%20Kai's%20ambitious%20hair%20routine%2C%20while%20others%20critiqued%20her%20product%20selection.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Geoff%20Weiss)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-housetruck-woods-washes-hair-freezing-criticism-eco-friendly-products-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Could%20'carbon%20passports'%20that%20limit%20how%20much%20we%20travel%20be%20in%20our%20future%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20plane%20flies%20in%20the%20sky%20against%20the%20background%20of%20green%20trees.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656a0f4386933e8fdb2eda3b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETsvetomir%20Hristov%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20recent%20report%20on%20the%20future%20of%20travel%20includes%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bcarbon%20passport.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20theory%2C%20a%20carbon%20passport%20would%20limit%20travelers'%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20each%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20travel-sustainability%20experts%20say%20there%20are%20more%20effective%20ways%20to%20support%20eco-friendly%20travel.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20climate%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ftourists-dumb-things-officials-deal-with-it-colosseum-naitonal-parks-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etourism%20problem%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20tour%20company%20is%20proposing%20a%20solution%3A%20a%20%26quot%3Bcarbon%20passport%26quot%3B%20that%20would%20limit%20how%20much%20carbon%20travelers%20could%20emit%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20October%20report%20written%20by%20the%20consultancy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thefuturelaboratory.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Future%20Laboratory%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20released%20by%20the%20travel%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.intrepidtravel.com%2Fus%2Fpurpose%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIntrepid%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggested%20the%20idea%20as%20a%20way%20to%20regulate%20travelers'%20annual%20emissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFigures%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fgreenvehicles%2Ffast-facts-transportation-greenhouse-gas-emissions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EEnvironmental%20Protection%20Agency%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20show%20that%2029%25%20of%20global%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20in%202021%20came%20from%20transportation%2C%20including%20flights%2C%20trains%2C%20and%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Paloma%20Zapata%20%E2%80%94%20the%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsustainabletravel.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESustainable%20Travel%20International%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20organization%20that%20develops%20strategies%20with%20governments%20and%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%20flights%20typically%20produce%20at%20least%20half%20of%20a%20trip's%20overall%20carbon%20footprint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20in%20the%20biggest%20race%20of%20our%20time%20%E2%80%94%20race%20to%20net-zero%20carbon%20emissions%2C%26quot%3B%20Zapata%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20when%20we%20travel%2C%20we%20consume%20a%20lot%20of%20resources.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20carbon%20passport%20would%20regulate%20travelers'%20emissions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlex%20Hawkins%2C%20the%20strategic-foresight%20editor%20at%20The%20Future%20Laboratory%20who%20spearheaded%20the%20report%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20concept%20might%20be%20necessary%20eventually%20if%20we%20didn't%20work%20toward%20a%20more%20sustainable%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20of%20carbon%20passports%20is%20based%20on%20the%20idea%20of%20personal%20carbon%20allowances%2C%26quot%3B%20Hawkins%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20would%20%26quot%3Bimpose%20a%20cap%20on%20how%20much%20carbon%20people%20are%20allowed%20to%20emit%20over%20a%20certain%20period%20of%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHawkins%20acknowledged%20that%20this%20wasn't%20a%20new%20concept.%20The%20UK%20Parliament%20outlined%20a%20similar%20idea%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublications.parliament.uk%2Fpa%2Fcm200708%2Fcmselect%2Fcmenvaud%2F565%2F565.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202008%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20%26quot%3BPersonal%20Carbon%20Trading.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BCarbon%20passports%20have%20taken%20that%20idea%20one%20step%20further%26quot%3B%20because%20they%20would%20involve%20tracking%20and%20limiting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-to-travel-more-sustainably-practices-tips-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etravel%20carbon%20emissions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20specifically%2C%20Hawkins%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20individuals%20needed%20to%20limit%20their%20carbon%20use%20to%202.3%20tons%20a%20year%20to%20mitigate%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20The%20average%20US%20citizen%20emits%2016%20tons%20annually%2C%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIn%20reality%2C%20a%20carbon%20passport%20would%20be%20challenging%20to%20implement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHawkins%20and%20Matt%20Berna%2C%20the%20president%20of%20Intrepid%20in%20the%20Americas%2C%20said%20they%20didn't%20see%20a%20carbon%20passport%20as%20a%20quick%20fix%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20future%20we%20don't%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20Hawkins%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BWe%20mapped%20out%20the%20concept%20as%20a%20provocation%20to%20say%20that%20if%20we%20aren't%20taking%20decisive%20action%20against%20the%20climate%20crisis%2C%20we%20are%20going%20to%20potentially%20see%20our%20freedoms%20curbed%20in%20different%20ways.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBerna%20said%20it's%20just%20one%20idea%20that%20could%20raise%20awareness%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fvenice-simplon-orient-express-train-review-luxury-sustainable-travel-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esustainable%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20work%2C%20such%20a%20passport%20would%20need%20to%20be%20created%20alongside%20new%20legislation%20and%20technological%20innovations%2C%20Berna%20and%20Hawkins%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20agreed%20making%20the%20concept%20a%20reality%20posed%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20is%20good%20in%20theory%2C%20but%20in%20terms%20of%20logistics%2C%20I%20don't%20see%20how%20it%20could%20come%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sps.nyu.edu%2Fhomepage%2Facademics%2Ffaculty-directory%2F17485-anna-abelson.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnna%20Abelson%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20adjunct%20professor%20of%20the%20Jonathan%20M.%20Tisch%20Center%20of%20Hospitality%20at%20New%20York%20University%2C%20told%20BI%2C%20speaking%20about%20how%20tracking%20would%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20tough%20to%20get%20enough%20people%20on%20board%2C%20Hawkins%20added%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bfor%20it%20to%20work%20internationally%2C%20it%20would%20require%20collaboration%20from%20a%20lot%20of%20different%20stakeholders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20were%20to%20put%20certain%20limits%20on%20our%20individual%20carbon%20emissions%2C%20that%20would%20have%20different%20ramifications%20for%20all%20of%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZapata%20said%20the%20restriction%20could%20be%20alienating%20and%20ineffective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20should%20be%20inspiring%20people%20to%20make%20changes%20and%20creating%20an%20environment%20for%20those%20changes%20to%20happen%20organically%26quot%3B%20by%20providing%20more%20sustainable%20options%20and%20raising%20awareness%20