cial%20response%20from%20the%20Indian%20side%20to%20the%20White%20House%E2%80%99s%20statement.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fpannun-assassination-plot-india-enquiry-committee-set-up%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20November%2029%2C%20US%20federal%20prosecutors%20filed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20fresh%20new%20charges%20against%20an%20Indian%20citizen%2C%20Nikhil%20Gupta%2C%20for%20being%20involved%20in%20a%20plot%20to%20kill%20a%20Sikh-American%20member%20of%20a%20Khalistani%20group%20which%20is%20banned%20by%20New%20Delhi.%20The%20charges%20also%20accuse%20an%20unnamed%20but%20%E2%80%9Cidentified%20Indian%20government%20employee%E2%80%9D%20of%20directing%20the%20failed%20plot.%20The%20indictment%20also%20appears%20to%20link%20the%20Indian%20official%20with%20the%20killing%20of%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%20a%20Canadian%20Khalistani%20activist%2C%20in%20June.%20A%20US%20undercover%20law%20enforcement%20personnel%20was%20allegedly%20recruited%20to%20be%20the%20hitman.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20charges%20did%20not%20name%20the%20Sikh-American%20citizen%2C%20he%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%2C%20general%20counsel%20of%20the%20proscribed%20group%2C%20%E2%80%98Sikhs%20for%20Justice%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20indictment%2C%20India%20had%20said%20that%20it%20was%20looking%20into%20the%20complaint%20and%20had%20set%20up%20an%20inquiry%20committee%20to%20investigate%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20US%20media%20reports%2C%20senior%20US%20administration%20officials%2C%20including%20NSA%20Jake%20Sullivan%20and%20CIA%20chief%20William%20Burns%2C%20had%20already%20raised%20the%20matter%20with%20the%20Indian%20government%20since%20August.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFiner%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20India%20is%20the%20first%20by%20a%20senior%20US%20administration%20official%20following%20the%20charges%20being%20made%20public.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20held%20talks%20with%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Ajit%20Doval%2C%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20and%20foreign%20secretary%20Vinay%20Kwatra.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fbriefings%2Fdepartment-press-briefing-december-4-2023%2F%23post-507198-INDIALAWENFORCEMENT%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20State%20Department%20on%20Monday%20also%20underlined%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20Washington%20was%20looking%20forward%20to%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20committee%20set%20up%20by%20the%20Indian%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20I%20would%20say%20that%20when%20these%20%E2%80%93%20when%20this%20alleged%20incident%20was%20brought%20to%20our%20attention%2C%20we%20made%20very%20clear%20at%20the%20most%20senior%20levels%20of%20our%20government%20to%20the%20most%20senior%20levels%20of%20the%20Indian%20Government%20how%20seriously%20we%20would%20treat%20something%20like%20this.%20They%20have%20opened%20an%20investigation%20into%20the%20matter%20and%20we%20look%20forward%20to%20seeing%20the%20results%20of%20that%20investigation%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20state%20department%20spokesperson%20Matthew%20Miller.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20the%20question%20about%20media%20reports%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20intelligence%20services%20conducting%20similar%20operations%20in%20neighbouring%20countries%2C%20Miller%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20made%20clear%20that%20we%20oppose%20transnational%20oppression%20no%20matter%20where%20it%20occurs%20or%20who%20might%20be%20conducting%20it.%20That%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20comment%20specific%20to%20India.%20That%E2%80%99s%20a%20comment%20specific%20to%20any%20country%20in%20the%20world.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701786887000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-conte