0%99%20which%20was%20later%20changed%20to%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EKam%20kiya%20dil%20se%2C%20Congress%20phir%20se%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98%20as%20the%20party%20leadership%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20disappoint%20the%20Sachin%20Pilot%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20this%20time%20the%20party%20failed%20to%20influence%20Gurjar%20votes%20in%20the%20state.%20Gurjars%2C%20Jats%2C%20Rajputs%2C%20and%20Meenas%20play%20key%20roles%20in%20forming%20the%20government.%20Gurjars%E2%80%99s%20anger%20is%20palpable%20over%20not%20handing%20over%20the%20reins%20to%20Pilot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20community%20holds%20influence%20over%20around%2030%20seats%2C%20mainly%20in%20the%20Karauli%2C%20Tonk%2C%20Hindaun%2C%20and%20Dausa%20districts%20of%20eastern%20Rajasthan.%20Out%20of%20the%2031%20seats%20that%20the%20Congress%20lost%20in%20the%20Rajasthan%20Assembly%20election%2C%2014%20come%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Felections%2Frajasthan-assembly%2Frajasthan-assembly-election-results-gujjar-disenchantment-costs-the-congress-dearly%2Farticle67602067.ece%5C%22%3Eeastern%20part%20of%20the%20state%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20Pilot%E2%80%99s%20community%2C%20the%20Gujjars%2C%20hold%20sway.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHigh-profile%20assembly%20seats%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmber%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Satish%20Poonia%2C%20a%20prominent%20Jat%20leader%20and%20former%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20in%20the%20state%2C%20lost%20to%20Prashanth%20Sharma%20by%20a%20margin%20of%209%2C092%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENathdwara%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20C.P.%20Joshi%2C%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20speaker%2C%20faced%20defeat%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20Vishvaraj%20Singh%20Mewar%20with%20a%20margin%20of%207504%20votes.%20Singh%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20royal%20family%20of%20Mewar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKota-North%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Shanti%20Dhariwal%2C%20a%20minister%20in%20the%20Ashok%20Gehlot%20government%2C%20managed%20to%20win%20the%20Kota-North%20seat%20with%20a%20narrow%20margin%20of%202%2C000%20votes%20from%20Prahlad%20Gunjal.%20Interestingly%2C%20this%20marks%20the%20first%20time%20Dhariwal%20secured%20the%20seat%20while%20Congress%20didn%E2%80%99t%20win%20the%20state%2C%20as%20he%20typically%20loses%20his%20constituency%20when%20Congress%20loses%20at%20the%20state%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECivil%20Lines%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Pratap%20Singh%20Khachariyawas%2C%20another%20minister%20in%20the%20Gehlot%20government%2C%20lost%20his%20seat%20with%20a%20significant%20margin%20of%2028%2C329%20votes%20to%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Gopal%20Sharma.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKaman%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Minister%20Zahida%20Khan%20also%20faced%20defeat%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Nauksham%20Choudhary.%20The%20people%20of%20Deeg%20had%20been%20demanding%20that%20Congress%20not%20give%20a%20ticket%20to%20Zahida%20Khan%2C%20especially%20after%20the%20killing%20of%20Junaid%20and%20Nasir%20in%20her%20constituency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20other%20prominent%20figures%20such%20as%20Pramod%20Jain%2C%20B.D.%20Kalla%20(Bikaner%20West)%2C%20Bhajan%20Lal%20Jatav%20(Weir)%2C%20Mamta%20Bhupesh%20(Sikrai)%2C%20Parsadi%20Lal%20Meena%20(Lalsot)%2C%20Sukhram%20Vishnoi%20(Sanchore)%2C%20and%20Ramlal%20Jat%20(Mandal)%20also%20lost%20their%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20seven-time%20BJP%20MLA%20and%20a%20significant%20figure%20in%20Rajasthan%20politics%2C%20Rajendra%20Rathore%2C%20was%20defeated%20from%20Taranagar%20by%20a%20margin%20of%2010%2C345%20votes%20to%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Narendra%20Budania.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20Taranagar%20was%20the%20only%20place%20where%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20campaigned%20for%20Congress%20on%20November%2016%2C%20just%20eight%20days%20before%20the%20voting%20on%20November%2025%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20time%20of%20ticket%20distribution%2C%20the%20senior%20leadership%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20happy%20with%20Gehlot%E2%80%99s%20decisions%20and%20influence%20in%20ticket%20distribution%2C%20which%20later%20resulted%20in%20significant%20losses%20for%20the%20party.%20Despite%20this%2C%20candidates%20like%20Shanti%20Dhariwal%20from%20Kota-North%20managed%20to%20secure%20a%20place%20in%20the%20Vidhan%20Sabha%2C%20even%20though%20senior%20leadership%20had%20questioned%20and%20alleged%20him%20as%20a%20corrupt%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERahul%20Gandhi%20was%20largely%20absent%20from%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20in%20Rajasthan.%20Though%20he%20referred%20to%20Rajasthan%20government%20welfare%20schemes%20during%20his%20campaign%20in%20other%20states%2C%20he%20did%20not%20hold%20any%20roadshow.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701776115000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F22112200%2FF84a12kXkAAI7Ua.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fgehlot-pilot-rivalry-congress-drubbing-rajasthan%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20Ashok%20Gehlot%20government%20appears%20to%20have%20received%20popular%20support%20for%20its%20welfare%20schemes%2C%20the%20Congress%20lost%20to%20the%20BJP%20due%20to%20its%20ineffective%20campaign%20strategy%20and%20poor%20selection%20of%20candidates.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fgehlot-pilot-rivalry-congress-drubbing-rajasthan%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ladakh%20Leaders'%20Statehood%20Demand%20Gets%20a%20Cold%20Shoulder%20From%20the%20Union%20Government%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F09125711%2Fvarun-nambiar-3SzqHcQ4eY0-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESrinagar%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Government%20of%20India%20is%20understood%20to%20have%20expressed%20its%20willingness%20to%20address%20Ladakh%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20on%20jobs%2C%20land%2C%20identity%20etc.%2C%20but%20it%20is%20unlikely%20to%20concede%20to%20the%20statehood%20demand%20for%20the%20union%20territory%20carved%20out%20in%202019.%20These%20indications%20came%20after%20a%20high-powered%20committee%20headed%20by%20Union%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20home%20affairs%20Nitayanad%20Rai%20met%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Tuesday%20to%20discuss%20the%20concerns%20and%20issues%20emerging%20in%20Ladakh%20since%20the%20August%202019%20decision%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20bifurcate%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20into%20two%20union%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMeeting%20and%20demands%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high-powered%20committee%2C%20which%20also%20includes%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20Apex%20Body%20Leh%20and%20Kargil%20Democratic%20Alliance%2C%20met%20in%20North%20Block%20on%20Tuesday%20after%20a%20gap%20of%20more%20than%20five%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meeting%2C%20the%20leaders%20from%20Leh%20and%20Kargil%20reiterated%20their%20four-point%20agenda%3A%20statehood%20for%20Ladakh%2C%20safeguards%20under%20the%20Sixth%20Schedule%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20two%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20for%20the%20union%20territory%20and%20employment%20opportunities%20for%20the%20youth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20representatives%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20didn%E2%80%99t%20give%20any%20assurance%20on%20fulfilling%20these%20demands%2C%20but%20told%20the%20leadership%20of%20Ladakh%20that%20talks%20will%20continue%20to%20address%20concerns%20of%20the%20people%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20learnt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20is%20understood%20to%20have%20told%20the%20delegation%20that%20the%20government%20will%20look%20at%20options%20on%20how%20to%20address%20their%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Chering%20Dorjay%2C%20former%20minister%20and%20member%20of%20Apex%20Body%20Leh%2C%20said%20they%20raised%20the%20four%20-point%20agenda%20during%20the%20meeting.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20minister%20listened%20to%20our%20demands%2C%20but%20neither%20rejected%20them%20nor%20accepted%20them.%20He%20told%20us%20that%20they%20will%20hold%20another%20meeting%20to%20discuss%20these%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20being%20asked%20about%20the%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20the%20statehood%20demand%2C%20Dorjay%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThey%20neither%20said%20yes%20nor%20no.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProminent%20political%20and%20social%20activist%20and%20member%20of%20the%20Kargil%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(KDA)%20Sajjad%20Kargili%20said%20that%20they%20told%20the%20Centre%20that%20these%20four%20demands%20should%20be%20met%20to%20fulfil%20the%20aspirations%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20told%20that%20the%20committee%20will%20meet%20again%20after%20the%20ongoing%20winter%20session%20is%20over%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CCold%E2%80%9D%20on%20statehood%20demand%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20what%20could%20indicate%20the%20BJP-led%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20cold%20attitude%20towards%20the%20demand%20for%20statehood%2C%20an%20official%20handout%20released%20after%20the%20talks%20didn%E2%80%99t%20mention%20that%20the%20issue%20was%20raised%20by%20the%20Ladakhi%20delegation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20ABL%20and%20KDA%20members%20submitted%20various%20issues%20pertaining%20to%20protection%20of%20rights%20of%20Ladakh%20residents%2C%20fast%20track%20recruitment%20processes%2C%20strengthening%20of%20LAHDCs%2C%20Greater%20participation%20in%20the%20decision%20making%20etc.%2C%E2%80%9D%20reads%20the%20official%20handout.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20said%20that%20New%20Delhi%20would%20continue%20talks%20with%20the%20ABL%20and%20KDA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CShri%20Rai%20said%20that%20the%20Government%20would%20continue%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20ABL%20and%20KDA%20and%20people%20of%20Ladakh%20for%20holistic%20and%20sustainable%20development%20of%20the%20UT%20of%20Ladakh%20on%20regular%20basis%2C%E2%80%9D%20reads%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20BJP%20MP%20from%20Ladakh%2C%20Jamyang%20Tsering%20Namgayal%2C%20has%20pushed%20for%20constitutional%20safeguards%20beyond%20the%20Sixth%20Schedule%20for%20safeguarding%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20identity%20and%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20firmly%20advocate%20the%20necessity%20for%20constitutional%20safeguards%20exceeding%20the%20provisions%20laid%20down%20in%20the%206th%20schedule%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20specifically%20tailored%20to%20safeguard%20the%20interests%20and%20aspirations%20of%20tribal%20people%20of%20Ladakh%2C%E2%80%9D%20reads%20the%20MP%E2%80%99s%20letter%20to%20the%20MoS%20home%20affairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Sixth%20Schedule%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20the%20autonomous%20district%20councils%20have%20specific%20legislative%2C%20executive%2C%20judicial%20and%20financial%20powers%20in%20the%20tribal%20areas%20of%20Meghalaya%2C%20Tripura%2C%20Mizoram%20and%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20such%20district%20has%20a%20council%2C%20which%20can%20make%20laws%20on%20certain%20specified%20matters%20like%20land%2C%20forests%2C%20canal%20water%2C%20shifting%20cultivation%2C%20village%20administration%2C%20inheritance%20of%20property%2C%20marriage%20and%20divorce%2C%20social%20customs%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20demand%20for%20Sixth%20Schedule%20implementation%20has%20become%20a%20rallying%20cry%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20especially%20in%20Buddhist-majority%20Leh%20district.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Leh%20district%20had%20welcomed%20UT%20status%20for%20Ladakh%20in%202019%2C%20Muslim-majority%20Kargil%20district%20had%20opposed%20it%20and%20observed%20a%20shutdown%20for%20several%20weeks%20to%20show%20its%20anger%20over%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunilateral%E2%80%9D%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20l